OL,3,CKazuo Ishiguro: I come up with book
OL,4,Ctitles by looking through cookbooks
OL,6,FSir Kazuo says that "you end up with
OL,7,Fthis kind of list of great titles that
OL,8,Fdon't have any works to go with them"
OL,9,F` citing opening up Peruvian novelist
OL,10,FMario Vargas Llosa's The War Of The
OL,11,FEnd Of The World and finding The Scene
OL,12,FOf A Strange Battle.
OL,14,FHe said: "I have to admit, sometimes
OL,15,FI've got the title, because it's a
OL,16,Fnear match to a story or book for
OL,17,Fwhich I don't have a title and, I
OL,18,Fthink If I just tweak that scene a
OL,19,Flittle bit and just have one of my
OL,20,Fcharacters utter this line then I
OL,21,Fcould use this great title."
